"Overall:  AMAZING!!   The can says it all, """so drinkable it is dangerous."""   My only knock on this beer is the availability.   I understand the buzz that is created with the elusive factor of beers like this, Pliny, Founder's KBS, etc.   And while the brewer John Kimmich has every right to keep this limited, I would suggest he brew more and make it available to more states (just a business take IMO).   Nevertheless, we ended up getting four cases between four people and have enjoyed this all summer down here in New Jersey, and will be back in VT next summer to get more (or sooner if we ski).   And while we had other great IPA's in Vermont such as Lawson's and Hill Farm Stand, this one (to me) is just so drinkable it is scary in a good way.  Cheers!!"
